# EasyCasa — Global Rules

You are working in a pnpm monorepo that deploys to a single VPS via Docker Compose + Caddy.

## Structure
- `/apps/web` — Next.js (TypeScript) frontend
- `/apps/api` — NestJS (TypeScript) backend
- `/services/ai` — Python FastAPI service (embeddings, valuation)
- `/packages/shared` — shared TypeScript types/config
- `/migration` — Phase 1 schema SQL + WordPress ETL tooling
- `/infra` — docker-compose, Caddy/Traefik, deploy & backup scripts
- `/docs` — specs. Read the relevant `/docs/<feature>.md` BEFORE writing code.

## Workflow
- One feature = one spec in `/docs` = one focused PR.
- Before finishing ANY task, run and pass: `pnpm lint`, `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm test`.
- Keep changes small and scoped to the task. Do not refactor unrelated code.

## Guardrails
- NEVER commit secrets. Real values live only in `.env` (git-ignored). Update `.env.example` and `/docs/env.md` when adding a variable.
- NEVER edit `/infra` deploy/secret handling without being explicitly asked.
- TypeScript is strict. No `any` unless justified with a comment.
- Prefer shared types from `@easycasa/shared` over duplicating shapes.

## Style
- Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`...).
- Small pure functions; explicit error handling; no silent catches.
